when they stop a running train?

00:03:07.354 --> 00:03:08.813 position:50% align:center
- But thanks to Koki,

00:03:08.897 --> 00:03:11.024 position:50% align:center
everything ended without getting
too serious.

00:03:11.107 --> 00:03:12.776 position:50% align:center
But it was definitely
terrifying!

00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:14.527 position:50% align:center
In all kinds of ways!

00:03:14.611 --> 00:03:16.237 position:50% align:center
[dog chomping]

00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:17.822 position:50% align:center
- And by the way,

00:03:17.906 --> 00:03:20.325 position:50% align:center
have any of the RBG guys
shown up here since then?

00:03:20.408 --> 00:03:22.327 position:50% align:center
 - No, they haven't come by.

00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:24.371 position:50% align:center
 Do you need to talk to them?
 - Yeah.

00:03:24.454 --> 00:03:27.040 position:50% align:center
 It seems those three
 got into another argument.

00:03:27.123 --> 00:03:29.501 position:50% align:center
So I thought I'd at least learn
the details.

00:03:29.584 --> 00:03:31.920 position:50% align:center
- Want me to go check up on them
for you?

00:03:32.003 --> 00:03:33.421 position:50% align:center
- That'd be a big help.

00:03:33.505 --> 00:03:35.757 position:50% align:center
Since we're so close to GourFes
I'm a bit busy.

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:38.218 position:50% align:center
- There's something I wanna
consult with them about as well.

00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:40.595 position:50% align:center
- Mari, are you gonna be okay
at GourFes being

00:03:40.679 --> 00:03:41.846 position:50% align:center
so laid back like that?

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:42.931 position:50% align:center
- Listen to him.

00:03:43.014 --> 00:03:44.766 position:50% align:center
Itadaki needs to win again.

00:03:44.849 --> 00:03:48.269 position:50% align:center
The back-to-back 24th ward
Gourmet Festival champions!

00:03:48.353 --> 00:03:50.605 position:50% align:center
- Uh, well, I don't know.
We'll see about that.

00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:52.232 position:50% align:center
- Put some spirit into it.

00:03:52.315 --> 00:03:53.775 position:50% align:center
The winner this year
is guaranteed

00:03:53.858 --> 00:03:56.236 position:50% align:center
a collaboration with
a major convenience store.

00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:57.779 position:50% align:center
Isn't that right, sir?

00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:59.572 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, correct.

00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:01.116 position:50% align:center
- You're part
of the executive committee,

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:03.451 position:50% align:center
Mr. Shirakaba.
Make Itadaki triumph!

00:04:03.535 --> 00:04:04.619 position:50% align:center
- I can't do that.

00:04:04.703 --> 00:04:05.870 position:50% align:center
- You're so square-headed.

00:04:05.954 --> 00:04:07.664 position:50% align:center
- I can't do what I can't do.

00:04:07.747 --> 00:04:09.207 position:50% align:center
- Koda-Gen--the famous
comedian--

00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:10.959 position:50% align:center
will be coming
to the Gourmet Festival.

00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.627 position:50% align:center
Can you please get me
an autograph?

00:04:12.711 --> 00:04:14.921 position:50% align:center
- Uh, shouldn't be hard.
I think I can do that much.

00:04:15.005 --> 00:04:17.090 position:50% align:center
- Takara Shopping Street's
future,

00:04:17.173 --> 00:04:19.134 position:50% align:center
it's all riding
on your Mari special!

00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.552 position:50% align:center
- A shock to the system

00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:22.137 position:50% align:center
to restart
the faintly-beating heart!

00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:24.222 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, I know all that.

00:04:24.305 --> 00:04:25.682 position:50% align:center
- So who's the competition?

00:04:25.765 --> 00:04:27.142 position:50% align:center
Are you worried
about Takara Mall?

00:04:27.225 --> 00:04:28.476 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.437 position:50% align:center
It's been six months since
it was built,

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.647 position:50% align:center
and our business
is getting tougher and tougher.

00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:35.942 position:50% align:center
- Why not try some monjayaki?

00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:38.111 position:50% align:center
It's the new soul food
of the 24th ward!

00:04:38.194 --> 00:04:41.322 position:50% align:center
- Pay with C-Pay
and you could get 85% cash back!

00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:44.075 position:50% align:center
- Also, they opened up all
the same types of shops as us.

00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:46.411 position:50% align:center
- Almost like they're trying
to put us out of business.

00:04:46.494 --> 00:04:48.413 position:50% align:center
- They've got a monjayaki spot

00:04:48.496 --> 00:04:50.874 position:50% align:center
competing against
our okonomiyaki place.

00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:54.544 position:50% align:center
- But our ward's okonomiyaki
has a totally different origin

00:04:54.627 --> 00:04:55.962 position:50% align:center
from inland Tokyo's,

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:58.381 position:50% align:center
so I see no point
in comparing ourselves to them.

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:00.842 position:50% align:center
- [laughing]

00:05:00.925 --> 00:05:02.552 position:50% align:center
These numbers show me the truth,

00:05:02.635 --> 00:05:05.889 position:50% align:center
but everybody else sees
a finely crafted illusion.

00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:07.515 position:50% align:center
Why, hello, there.

00:05:07.599 --> 00:05:08.600 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:05:08.683 --> 00:05:10.185 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:11.895 position:50% align:center
Everything's going perfectly.

00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:14.773 position:50% align:center
I can give you the details
in the weekly report.

00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.900 position:50% align:center
Yes, I'm already aware
of all that.

00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:19.152 position:50% align:center
We'll keep it legal.
No violence.

00:05:19.235 --> 00:05:20.737 position:50% align:center
Meet all conditions.

00:05:20.820 --> 00:05:23.031 position:50% align:center
So please use us
for construction.

00:05:23.114 --> 00:05:25.658 position:50% align:center
Yes, it's a pleasure
doing business with you.

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.538 position:50% align:center
- Originally from the 24th ward,

00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:32.540 position:50% align:center
 global artist Zeroth is back
 in the news.

00:05:32.624 --> 00:05:35.085 position:50% align:center
 His graffiti satirizing
 the human rights movement

00:05:35.168 --> 00:05:37.045 position:50% align:center
 was found in Washington, D.C.

00:05:37.128 --> 00:05:38.755 position:50% align:center
 - I stumbled upon this
 in the morning

00:05:38.838 --> 00:05:39.964 position:50% align:center
 and the moment I saw it,

00:05:40.048 --> 00:05:41.424 position:50% align:center
 I knew it had to be Zeroth!

00:05:41.508 --> 00:05:44.094 position:50% align:center
- I can't believe his identity
is still a mystery.

00:05:44.177 --> 00:05:46.096 position:50% align:center
- His art,
it's heartfelt.

00:05:46.179 --> 00:05:47.681 position:50% align:center
- [chomping]
 - Our next story.

00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:49.474 position:50% align:center
 People are raising
 doubts concerning

00:05:49.557 --> 00:05:50.850 position:50% align:center
 the autonomous driving

00:05:50.934 --> 00:05:51.976 position:50% align:center
 of the rainbow line
 Kizuna train.

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:53.853 position:50% align:center
- That story again.

00:05:53.937 --> 00:05:56.898 position:50% align:center
It's a really lucky thing Mari
was safe at the end of the day.

00:05:56.981 --> 00:05:59.401 position:50% align:center
- [grunting]
- Hey Shu, can you help me out?

00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:00.777 position:50% align:center
Please!
- [groans]

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:03.738 position:50% align:center
[groans]
Hmm?

00:06:03.822 --> 00:06:06.199 position:50% align:center
- I need to come up with ideas
for the gourmet festival,

00:06:06.282 --> 00:06:07.617 position:50% align:center
and it's this weekend!

00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:09.494 position:50% align:center
 - [groans]
 Ow.

00:06:09.577 --> 00:06:12.080 position:50% align:center
- Jeez, are you even listening
to me right now?

00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:14.082 position:50% align:center
What?
Do you have muscle cramps?

00:06:14.165 --> 00:06:16.710 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, my body's feeling
really heavy ever since

00:06:16.793 --> 00:06:18.586 position:50% align:center
that thing happened
two days ago.

00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:21.423 position:50% align:center
- Shu, you already have
monstrous athletic skill,

00:06:21.506 --> 00:06:23.091 position:50% align:center
but on that train track,

00:06:23.174 --> 00:06:25.135 position:50% align:center
you looked like a super hero
from a comic!

00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:27.387 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
What are you talkin' about?

00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:31.433 position:50% align:center
All that happened
when I received a call

00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:33.977 position:50% align:center
on my phone from Asumi,
and after that call,

00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:36.271 position:50% align:center
I don't know why,
but I could really move.

00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:39.399 position:50% align:center
- What do you mean, Shu?
A phone call from Asumi?

00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:41.735 position:50% align:center
- I really don't understand it
at all, either,

00:06:41.818 --> 00:06:45.113 position:50% align:center
and yet that was without
any doubt truly her voice.

00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:46.614 position:50% align:center
At least, I think.

00:06:46.698 --> 00:06:48.533 position:50% align:center
- Do you understand what
you're telling me right now?

00:06:48.616 --> 00:06:50.577 position:50% align:center
You think you got a call
from a dead person.

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:52.245 position:50% align:center
- I know it's crazy.

00:06:52.328 --> 00:06:55.165 position:50% align:center
However, when I picked up
that phone call,

00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:57.709 position:50% align:center
these images popped into
my head somehow.

00:06:57.792 --> 00:07:01.421 position:50% align:center
 An image of you being run over
 by the Kizuna train.

00:07:01.504 --> 00:07:04.049 position:50% align:center
Oh, and don't repeat this stuff
to anyone.

00:07:04.132 --> 00:07:05.884 position:50% align:center
I seriously don't understand it.

00:07:05.967 --> 00:07:08.553 position:50% align:center
- You don't have to tell me.
Such a story.

00:07:08.636 --> 00:07:11.681 position:50% align:center
Oh, but this means I
was rescued thanks

00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:12.766 position:50% align:center
to all of that.

00:07:14.893 --> 00:07:17.562 position:50% align:center
So, did you try
to call her back later?

00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:19.731 position:50% align:center
- I did,
so many times.

00:07:20.648 --> 00:07:22.192 position:50% align:center
But it goes
to voicemail every time.

00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:26.571 position:50% align:center
- This is a lot.

00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:29.199 position:50% align:center
It's hard to make sense
of all my feelings.

00:07:30.116 --> 00:07:31.451 position:50% align:center
- Same here.

00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:33.536 position:50% align:center
And I can't help
but think about it.

00:07:33.620 --> 00:07:35.080 position:50% align:center
 - [exhales]

00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:37.248 position:50% align:center
This is no time to be creating
a new menu item.

00:07:37.332 --> 00:07:38.291 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:40.043 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah.

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:42.379 position:50% align:center
You need to smooth things over
with both Ran and Koki sometime.

00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.130 position:50% align:center
By the way,

00:07:44.214 --> 00:07:45.715 position:50% align:center
I think it was simply
a prank call.

00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.217 position:50% align:center
See ya.
- [stammers]

00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:49.886 position:50% align:center
Why exactly do you know about
the argument we had?

00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:52.764 position:50% align:center
- When it concerns Asumi,

00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:54.724 position:50% align:center
you really stop thinking
about anything else.

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:59.062 position:50% align:center
Can't you see that Asumi's
no longer with us?

00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:02.399 position:50% align:center
- What?
Even you, Mari?

00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:04.943 position:50% align:center
If Asumi is actually still alive
then it's something

00:08:05.026 --> 00:08:07.570 position:50% align:center
to be genuinely happy about.
[grunts]

00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:13.993 position:50% align:center
[grunting]

00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:15.704 position:50% align:center
- Where you wanna eat?

00:08:15.787 --> 00:08:17.288 position:50% align:center
- Itadaki should do.

00:08:17.372 --> 00:08:19.082 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]
Mari has--

00:08:19.165 --> 00:08:21.292 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Team practice today.

00:08:21.376 --> 00:08:23.336 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
So there's no Mari special.

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:25.005 position:50% align:center
- Ah, really?
That's too bad.

00:08:25.088 --> 00:08:27.173 position:50% align:center
- Mr. 24, you've gotta help me!
- Huh?

00:08:27.257 --> 00:08:29.634 position:50% align:center
- I need the powers
of a super hero!

00:08:29.718 --> 00:08:31.094 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]

00:08:31.177 --> 00:08:33.513 position:50% align:center
- [grunting]

00:08:33.596 --> 00:08:35.432 position:50% align:center
- Way to go, goal keeper!

00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:36.808 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Asumi,

00:08:36.891 --> 00:08:38.893 position:50% align:center
this isn't exactly what
a hero does.

00:08:38.977 --> 00:08:41.396 position:50% align:center
- And yet you do it.
[laughs]

00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:42.647 position:50% align:center
- I mean, yeah, you can't have

00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:44.357 position:50% align:center
a soccer game without
a goal keeper.

00:08:44.441 --> 00:08:45.817 position:50% align:center
- [laughing]

00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:47.110 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]
- [giggles]

00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:49.696 position:50% align:center
- [grunting]

00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:52.991 position:50% align:center
- Hooray, I knew it!
Mr. 24!

00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:54.909 position:50% align:center
[all laughing]
- That's a dirty trick,

00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.786 position:50% align:center
you guys!
- What are you doing, Mari?

00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:58.079 position:50% align:center
Come on!
Let's get going!

00:08:58.163 --> 00:08:59.581 position:50% align:center
- Okay!

00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:02.334 position:50% align:center
 [upbeat music]

00:09:02.417 --> 00:09:04.544 position:50% align:center
It's Asumi?
- Eh?

00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:07.797 position:50% align:center
Asumi's my motif.
So, how's it look?

00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.008 position:50% align:center
- It's good.
It definitely looks like her.

00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:12.385 position:50% align:center
But she looks kind of mature.

00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:13.845 position:50% align:center
- That's what I was going for,
actually.

00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:14.888 position:50% align:center
- I see.

00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:18.433 position:50% align:center
A souvenir.

00:09:18.516 --> 00:09:20.435 position:50% align:center
They're bread crusts
from the Aoi Bakery.

00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:22.896 position:50% align:center
[beeps]

00:09:23.438 --> 00:09:25.106 position:50% align:center
- Since you're already here,
come on in.

00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:27.150 position:50% align:center
[all muttering]

00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:29.527 position:50% align:center
- Uh, hi, everybody.

00:09:29.611 --> 00:09:32.197 position:50% align:center
- Hey there, Mari.
It's good to see you.

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.240 position:50% align:center
- Kinako!
It's been a while.

00:09:34.324 --> 00:09:36.368 position:50% align:center
This place is pretty amazing.

00:09:36.451 --> 00:09:38.995 position:50% align:center
- Is this your first time being
in the DoRed hideout?

00:09:39.079 --> 00:09:41.873 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, it really feels like
a secret base.

00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:44.668 position:50% align:center
- That's the point.
S.A.R.G. has eyes on us.

00:09:44.751 --> 00:09:47.837 position:50% align:center
Our members are anonymous
and never show their faces.

00:09:47.921 --> 00:09:51.174 position:50% align:center
Not to mention everyone living
in Shantytown is on our side.

00:09:51.257 --> 00:09:53.218 position:50% align:center
So they shouldn't find out who
we are that easily.

00:09:53.301 --> 00:09:54.511 position:50% align:center
[chomps]

00:09:54.594 --> 00:09:56.721 position:50% align:center
- Hey, were you okay
the other day?

00:09:56.805 --> 00:09:59.099 position:50% align:center
S.A.R.G. totally reprimanded
you afterwards, didn't they?

00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:00.684 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.

00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:02.644 position:50% align:center
Like, they wanted to know who
it was that saved me

00:10:02.727 --> 00:10:04.979 position:50% align:center
and what my relationship
to DoRed is.

00:10:05.063 --> 00:10:07.524 position:50% align:center
- Did you tell 'em anything
about Shu?

00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:09.776 position:50% align:center
- No way.
Shu asked me not to.

00:10:09.859 --> 00:10:11.111 position:50% align:center
- Well anyway,

00:10:11.194 --> 00:10:12.612 position:50% align:center
I'm really glad
that you're all right.

00:10:12.696 --> 00:10:15.657 position:50% align:center
 - But what in the world
 was that strange vision?

00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:18.785 position:50% align:center
 It looked like Asumi
 and it told me to choose one

00:10:18.868 --> 00:10:20.704 position:50% align:center
 of two futures.

00:10:20.787 --> 00:10:23.540 position:50% align:center
 So does that mean we changed
 the future back there?

00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.250 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Ran.
- Hmm?

00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:26.835 position:50% align:center
Oh, sorry.
It's nothin'.

00:10:26.918 --> 00:10:28.545 position:50% align:center
I just zoned out.
- Ran,

00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:30.213 position:50% align:center
your expression's kind
of erotic.

00:10:30.296 --> 00:10:31.297 position:50% align:center
- Cut that out.

00:10:31.381 --> 00:10:33.383 position:50% align:center
- Oh, heads up!

00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:34.884 position:50% align:center
It's almost time
for us to start!

00:10:34.968 --> 00:10:37.053 position:50% align:center
- Oh?
Time to start what?

00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:39.597 position:50% align:center
both: We're about to begin
a live painting stream.

00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:41.808 position:50% align:center
- There's already
30,000 people waiting.

00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:43.059 position:50% align:center
- Ooh.

00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:44.269 position:50% align:center
Well then,
I'll get going.

00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:45.353 position:50% align:center
Good luck with your stream!

00:10:45.437 --> 00:10:46.479 position:50% align:center
- Thank you!

00:10:47.272 --> 00:10:48.773 position:50% align:center
See ya later.

00:10:48.857 --> 00:10:50.775 position:50% align:center
[door opens and closes]
Mm?

00:10:51.818 --> 00:10:53.445 position:50% align:center
All right, then, Kinako,

00:10:53.528 --> 00:10:55.196 position:50% align:center
let's get this show started.

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50% align:center
- Yeah!

00:10:58.616 --> 00:10:59.909 position:50% align:center
- Listen.

00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:02.829 position:50% align:center
I don't know if little old me
is suited for this.

00:11:02.912 --> 00:11:04.748 position:50% align:center
- But you look like
you're havin' fun.

00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:06.332 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, you're totally on
a roll.

00:11:06.416 --> 00:11:08.251 position:50% align:center
- Wh--are you kidding me?
Not at all!

00:11:08.335 --> 00:11:11.171 position:50% align:center
True art only happens when
you're expressing your attitude.

00:11:11.254 --> 00:11:12.589 position:50% align:center
If you're drawing
on some legal wall,

00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:14.299 position:50% align:center
that's not cool or daring.

00:11:14.382 --> 00:11:16.051 position:50% align:center
- That's totally missing
the point.

00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:18.678 position:50% align:center
What really matters
is that your art echoes

00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:20.722 position:50% align:center
with people's hearts whether
or not it's legal.

00:11:20.805 --> 00:11:23.141 position:50% align:center
I think more people should get
to look at it.

00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:26.853 position:50% align:center
- Those words echo within
my own heart even louder.

00:11:26.936 --> 00:11:29.272 position:50% align:center
Here, finished!

00:11:29.356 --> 00:11:32.817 position:50% align:center
- Uh, can I, you know, like,
take a picture, maybe?

00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:34.444 position:50% align:center
- Hmm?
Okay.

00:11:34.527 --> 00:11:35.820 position:50% align:center
Take as many as you want.

00:11:35.904 --> 00:11:37.655 position:50% align:center
- Wow, thank you so much!

00:11:37.739 --> 00:11:39.657 position:50% align:center
Um, if you don't mind,

00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:41.201 position:50% align:center
can I take a video
at some point?

00:11:41.284 --> 00:11:43.453 position:50% align:center
- A video?
- Yeah, like a live painting!

00:11:43.536 --> 00:11:44.954 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- Wonderful!

00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:46.790 position:50% align:center
- Cool!
Sounds good!

00:11:46.873 --> 00:11:48.166 position:50% align:center
That's perfect!
- [groans]

00:11:52.921 --> 00:11:54.422 position:50% align:center
[knocking]
- Uh?

00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:55.882 position:50% align:center
Oh, hi, Mari.

00:11:55.965 --> 00:11:57.008 position:50% align:center
- Hey, there.

00:11:57.092 --> 00:11:58.218 position:50% align:center
Studying for classes?

00:11:58.885 --> 00:12:00.178 position:50% align:center
- I'm sorry.

00:12:00.261 --> 00:12:02.263 position:50% align:center
I only allow emergency
notifications

00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:03.807 position:50% align:center
when I'm doing my homework.

00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:05.433 position:50% align:center
I'm surprised you found me here.

00:12:05.517 --> 00:12:08.311 position:50% align:center
- I called the Suido house
and Miss Tsuzuragawa.

00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:10.814 position:50% align:center
- I see.
So, what's up?

00:12:10.897 --> 00:12:12.565 position:50% align:center
Is it something really urgent?

00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:15.235 position:50% align:center
- I heard you had an argument
with Shu two days ago.

00:12:15.318 --> 00:12:17.362 position:50% align:center
Mr. Shirakaba's
pretty concerned.

00:12:17.445 --> 00:12:19.989 position:50% align:center
- So that's what this is about.
You came here to mediate.

00:12:20.073 --> 00:12:21.199 position:50% align:center
- Have you decided what
to order?

00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:23.076 position:50% align:center
- Oh, one blend coffee, please.

00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:25.662 position:50% align:center
- One blend coffee.
Will that be all for you?

00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:27.622 position:50% align:center
- Uh-huh.
- All right.

00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:29.624 position:50% align:center
Hang tight.
It'll be just a moment.

00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:32.210 position:50% align:center
- Anyway, it's not really why
I came here.

00:12:32.293 --> 00:12:33.670 position:50% align:center
I've got a question for you.

00:12:33.753 --> 00:12:34.879 position:50% align:center
How do I put it?

00:12:36.506 --> 00:12:38.508 position:50% align:center
How much do you know about that
Mon Jungle place

00:12:38.591 --> 00:12:40.218 position:50% align:center
in the Takara Mall?
- Hmm?

00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:42.470 position:50% align:center
Wait, you're asking me about
their flagship restaurant?

00:12:42.554 --> 00:12:43.680 position:50% align:center
- That's right.

00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.265 position:50% align:center
Apparently we two
are considered

00:12:45.348 --> 00:12:47.017 position:50% align:center
the favorites to win
the Gourmet Festival.

00:12:47.100 --> 00:12:49.019 position:50% align:center
 - Gourmet Festival.

00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:50.854 position:50% align:center
 It's already that time
 of the year again, huh?

00:12:52.772 --> 00:12:55.191 position:50% align:center
Check out the 24th ward's
GourFes!

00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:59.320 position:50% align:center
The 24th ward Gourmet Festival!
Please, come take a look.

00:12:59.904 --> 00:13:02.073 position:50% align:center
The 24th ward Gourmet Festival.

00:13:02.157 --> 00:13:04.284 position:50% align:center
[groaning]

00:13:05.076 --> 00:13:07.537 position:50% align:center
I can barely get anybody
to take these fliers.

00:13:07.620 --> 00:13:08.913 position:50% align:center
This is bad.

00:13:08.997 --> 00:13:10.498 position:50% align:center
I promised father
I would make it a success.

00:13:10.582 --> 00:13:12.000 position:50% align:center
- Hey!
- Asumi.

00:13:12.083 --> 00:13:14.044 position:50% align:center
Aren't you in charge
of the Nihima Station area?

00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.545 position:50% align:center
- I finished passing them
all out!

00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:17.839 position:50% align:center
- [groans]
- Hey, why the long face?

00:13:17.922 --> 00:13:20.300 position:50% align:center
Nobody's going to accept fliers
if you look like that.

00:13:20.383 --> 00:13:21.718 position:50% align:center
Smile, smile!

00:13:21.801 --> 00:13:23.553 position:50% align:center
- What do you mean?
Like this?

00:13:23.636 --> 00:13:24.721 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.514 position:50% align:center
Maybe just a bit differently.

00:13:26.598 --> 00:13:28.141 position:50% align:center
- Looks like you need help.
- [grunts]

00:13:28.224 --> 00:13:29.726 position:50% align:center
You should have asked us
for a hand.

00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:31.603 position:50% align:center
- Oh, hi, Mari.
- She's right.

00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.480 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- Let's make Gourmet Festival

00:13:33.563 --> 00:13:34.981 position:50% align:center
a hit.
- Are those the fliers

00:13:35.065 --> 00:13:36.107 position:50% align:center
we need to pass out?

00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:38.735 position:50% align:center
- You bet.
Well, for today, at least.

00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:40.653 position:50% align:center
[indistinct chatter]
- Asumi.

00:13:40.737 --> 00:13:42.572 position:50% align:center
Did you reach out to everyone?

00:13:42.655 --> 00:13:44.157 position:50% align:center
- Of course I did.

00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:45.784 position:50% align:center
Come on.
We should pass them out, too.

00:13:45.867 --> 00:13:47.786 position:50% align:center
- Y--Yeah.

00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:48.912 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:48.995 --> 00:13:50.246 position:50% align:center
Thank you all so much.

00:13:51.039 --> 00:13:52.290 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:13:52.374 --> 00:13:54.459 position:50% align:center
- Oh, right there!
That's a good smile.

00:13:54.542 --> 00:13:56.169 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:13:58.088 --> 00:13:59.756 position:50% align:center
- I really learned
a lot about being part

00:13:59.839 --> 00:14:02.008 position:50% align:center
of operations as a member
of the executive committee.

00:14:02.092 --> 00:14:03.426 position:50% align:center
- Oh.

00:14:03.510 --> 00:14:05.053 position:50% align:center
 That's right.
 How could I forget?

00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:07.430 position:50% align:center
 Koki is involved
 so he can't really side

00:14:07.514 --> 00:14:08.640 position:50% align:center
 with anyone in particular.

00:14:08.723 --> 00:14:09.808 position:50% align:center
- Hang on.

00:14:09.891 --> 00:14:11.351 position:50% align:center
You were asking me
about something.

00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.228 position:50% align:center
- Uh, no, it's fine!

00:14:13.311 --> 00:14:15.021 position:50% align:center
I was simply talking about
how GourFes will be

00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:17.315 position:50% align:center
hyped up again this year.
[giggles]

00:14:18.525 --> 00:14:20.026 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]
- Mr. Koki.

00:14:20.110 --> 00:14:22.237 position:50% align:center
I've kept you waiting.

00:14:22.737 --> 00:14:24.406 position:50% align:center
- Sorry to be troubling you.

00:14:24.489 --> 00:14:26.324 position:50% align:center
 - No need for you
 to worry about it. 

00:14:26.408 --> 00:14:27.951 position:50% align:center
 - Well, anyways,
 I thought I told you--

00:14:28.034 --> 00:14:29.744 position:50% align:center
- About that call you received.

00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:32.205 position:50% align:center
We've not yet identified
the culprit.

00:14:32.288 --> 00:14:34.916 position:50% align:center
But there seems to be someone
duping Asumi's number.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:36.042 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]

00:14:36.126 --> 00:14:37.585 position:50% align:center
- We'll continue investigating.

00:14:37.669 --> 00:14:38.962 position:50% align:center
- Oh.
I see.

00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:40.588 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:14:40.672 --> 00:14:42.924 position:50% align:center
 That phone call
 and the premonition

00:14:43.008 --> 00:14:45.635 position:50% align:center
 and that power which coursed
 through my body,

00:14:45.719 --> 00:14:48.763 position:50% align:center
 the scoundrel pretending
 to be Asumi must hold

00:14:48.847 --> 00:14:50.974 position:50% align:center
 the key to unraveling
 all these secrets.

00:14:51.057 --> 00:14:53.143 position:50% align:center
 [tense music]

00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:56.521 position:50% align:center
- I can't believe
Gourmet Festival

00:14:56.604 --> 00:14:58.023 position:50% align:center
is this weekend.

00:14:58.106 --> 00:14:59.607 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna run out of time.

00:14:59.691 --> 00:15:02.068 position:50% align:center
[groans]
Oh.

00:15:02.152 --> 00:15:05.238 position:50% align:center
Is that Mr. Shirakaba
and Mr. Chikushi from S.A.R.G.?

00:15:07.282 --> 00:15:09.200 position:50% align:center
- Okay, Mr. Shirakaba.

00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:10.910 position:50% align:center
What is it that you wanted
to ask me?

00:15:10.994 --> 00:15:12.996 position:50% align:center
- What's Takara Mall--I mean,

00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:15.373 position:50% align:center
what's Yabusame want
to accomplish?

00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:18.460 position:50% align:center
- Kaba, how did you hear
about Yabusame?

00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:20.628 position:50% align:center
- It's a quasi-gang
organization, right?

00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:22.130 position:50% align:center
Someone I used to know
is a part of it.

00:15:22.213 --> 00:15:23.631 position:50% align:center
- I see.

00:15:23.715 --> 00:15:25.133 position:50% align:center
 - Why in the world
 am I doing something

00:15:25.216 --> 00:15:26.718 position:50% align:center
 as sneaky as eavesdropping?

00:15:26.801 --> 00:15:27.927 position:50% align:center
[dog whimpers]
[shushes]

00:15:28.011 --> 00:15:29.846 position:50% align:center
- When it comes to Takara Mall,
well,

00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:31.723 position:50% align:center
Yabusame owns and operates it,

00:15:31.806 --> 00:15:33.641 position:50% align:center
though only through
a shell company.

00:15:33.725 --> 00:15:35.685 position:50% align:center
- What's Yabusame after
when it comes

00:15:35.769 --> 00:15:37.771 position:50% align:center
to the 24th ward GourFes?

00:15:37.854 --> 00:15:39.647 position:50% align:center
Don't you think that it's a bit
too much money

00:15:39.731 --> 00:15:42.525 position:50% align:center
to be moving around?
- The past couple years,

00:15:42.609 --> 00:15:45.320 position:50% align:center
they've been making money
in shady ways as land sharks

00:15:45.403 --> 00:15:47.447 position:50% align:center
receiving construction
contracts.

00:15:47.530 --> 00:15:50.158 position:50% align:center
- Their objective is to buy up
Takara Shopping Street?

00:15:50.241 --> 00:15:53.370 position:50% align:center
- Mon Jungle which is operated
by Yabusame will not pull

00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:55.163 position:50% align:center
their punches in order
to win first place.

00:15:55.246 --> 00:15:56.456 position:50% align:center
Isn't the mall supposed

00:15:56.539 --> 00:15:58.124 position:50% align:center
to be under Suido Corporation's
wing?

00:15:58.583 --> 00:15:59.959 position:50% align:center
Wait.
- Hold up.

00:16:00.043 --> 00:16:02.087 position:50% align:center
I can't officially make
any further comments.

00:16:02.170 --> 00:16:03.672 position:50% align:center
It's about time I get going.

00:16:05.215 --> 00:16:07.425 position:50% align:center
- [exhales]
- The heck's going on here?

00:16:07.509 --> 00:16:08.718 position:50% align:center
- Uh, Mari!

00:16:09.803 --> 00:16:11.137 position:50% align:center
You were listening?

00:16:11.554 --> 00:16:12.889 position:50% align:center
- [grunting]

00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:14.808 position:50% align:center
- Mr. Shirakaba!

00:16:14.891 --> 00:16:16.726 position:50% align:center
Why did that conversation make
it sound like the outcome

00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:18.561 position:50% align:center
of GourFes was already decided?

00:16:18.645 --> 00:16:20.855 position:50% align:center
- Jeez Louise, Mari.
You're way too smart.

00:16:20.939 --> 00:16:22.440 position:50% align:center
- Don't mock me!
- No need to worry.

00:16:22.524 --> 00:16:24.484 position:50% align:center
I will not let there be
any dishonesty.

00:16:24.567 --> 00:16:25.777 position:50% align:center
You can trust me.

00:16:27.362 --> 00:16:28.363 position:50% align:center
- I believe you.

00:16:28.446 --> 00:16:29.948 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:16:30.031 --> 00:16:32.409 position:50% align:center
But sir, why
is everything you do always

00:16:32.492 --> 00:16:33.868 position:50% align:center
for somebody else?

00:16:33.952 --> 00:16:35.745 position:50% align:center
Even though you're
no longer our teacher,

00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:37.080 position:50% align:center
you keep us in mind.
- [groans]

00:16:37.163 --> 00:16:39.624 position:50% align:center
- It's my personality.
Well...

00:16:40.542 --> 00:16:42.669 position:50% align:center
 I guess it's my beliefs.

00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:45.171 position:50% align:center
Is it true you guys
have been playing after school

00:16:45.255 --> 00:16:47.382 position:50% align:center
at the abandoned
Takara Elementary building?

00:16:47.465 --> 00:16:49.217 position:50% align:center
They're demolishing it
in the redevelopment,

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:50.885 position:50% align:center
so don't go near it anymore.

00:16:50.969 --> 00:16:52.679 position:50% align:center
[all speaking at once]

00:16:52.762 --> 00:16:55.223 position:50% align:center
- That school has a history
within the 24th ward.

00:16:55.306 --> 00:16:56.683 position:50% align:center
Why would they demolish it?

00:16:56.766 --> 00:16:58.184 position:50% align:center
- It's full
of childhood memories.

00:16:58.268 --> 00:16:59.978 position:50% align:center
- All of you be quiet.
- That building can definitely

00:17:00.061 --> 00:17:01.730 position:50% align:center
still be used.
- That's not the point.

00:17:01.813 --> 00:17:03.606 position:50% align:center
The school closed because
of low birth rates.

00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:05.400 position:50% align:center
- So what?
At least reuse it

00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:07.068 position:50% align:center
for something else, then.
- What are you going to do

00:17:07.152 --> 00:17:09.529 position:50% align:center
if you get hurt trespassing
in a place that's off limits?

00:17:09.612 --> 00:17:11.573 position:50% align:center
Stop throwing a tantrum!

00:17:11.656 --> 00:17:14.367 position:50% align:center
- Now it is time to start
the meeting for the conservation

00:17:14.451 --> 00:17:16.327 position:50% align:center
of the Takara Elementary School
building!

00:17:16.411 --> 00:17:18.329 position:50% align:center
Everyone, speak your opinions.

00:17:18.413 --> 00:17:20.623 position:50% align:center
- Mm, well, the fact that it's

00:17:20.707 --> 00:17:22.709 position:50% align:center
a school with our memories
is huge.

00:17:22.792 --> 00:17:25.211 position:50% align:center
Plus it still serves
as a place where kids relax.

00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:26.713 position:50% align:center
- Ooh, and don't forget,

00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:28.506 position:50% align:center
there's that historical bit.
- Right.

00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:31.009 position:50% align:center
Takara was the first
of its kind.

00:17:31.092 --> 00:17:32.594 position:50% align:center
It was the first school
constructed

00:17:32.677 --> 00:17:35.805 position:50% align:center
on this island after the war
when it became the 24th ward.

00:17:35.889 --> 00:17:38.892 position:50% align:center
- Also, I've got memories
of my mother there.

00:17:38.975 --> 00:17:40.643 position:50% align:center
- Mrs. Suido, of course.

00:17:40.727 --> 00:17:42.020 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:17:42.103 --> 00:17:43.480 position:50% align:center
We've gotta preserve
that building.

00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:45.482 position:50% align:center
In honor of your mom's memory
as well.

00:17:45.565 --> 00:17:47.233 position:50% align:center
- Thanks for waiting, everyone.

00:17:47.317 --> 00:17:49.861 position:50% align:center
Today's Mari special
is a blackboard.

00:17:49.944 --> 00:17:51.738 position:50% align:center
Enjoy drawing to your heart's
content!

00:17:51.821 --> 00:17:53.990 position:50% align:center
- Well, that leaves
a visual impact.

00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:55.658 position:50% align:center
- Is it black because
it's burnt?

00:17:55.742 --> 00:17:57.035 position:50% align:center
- It looks great.
- Huh?

00:17:57.118 --> 00:17:58.328 position:50% align:center
- I'm gonna start drawin'
right now.

00:17:58.411 --> 00:17:59.662 position:50% align:center
- Wait a second!
This is it!

00:17:59.746 --> 00:18:00.914 position:50% align:center
It's perfect!

00:18:00.997 --> 00:18:02.999 position:50% align:center
This is just the idea
we needed, Mari!

00:18:03.083 --> 00:18:06.336 position:50% align:center
 We should cover the Takara
Elementary School with graffiti!

00:18:06.419 --> 00:18:09.297 position:50% align:center
 [upbeat music]

00:18:09.381 --> 00:18:16.304 position:50% align:center
 ♪ ♪

00:18:18.306 --> 00:18:19.933 position:50% align:center
- Spread the word, everyone.

00:18:20.016 --> 00:18:21.434 position:50% align:center
And posted.

00:18:21.518 --> 00:18:28.441 position:50% align:center
 ♪ ♪

00:18:32.153 --> 00:18:34.823 position:50% align:center
- Today's movement draws meaning
from preserving

00:18:34.906 --> 00:18:36.449 position:50% align:center
a historical building

00:18:36.533 --> 00:18:38.535 position:50% align:center
 and deepening the bonds
 for the community members

00:18:38.618 --> 00:18:39.536 position:50% align:center
 of this area.

00:18:39.619 --> 00:18:40.745 position:50% align:center
- [chewing]

00:18:40.829 --> 00:18:42.580 position:50% align:center
- Hey, so what do you think,
sir?

00:18:42.664 --> 00:18:46.042 position:50% align:center
When RGB all gather up,
then nothing is impossible.

00:18:46.126 --> 00:18:47.961 position:50% align:center
[all chuckling]

00:18:48.461 --> 00:18:49.879 position:50% align:center
- [chuckles]

00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:51.840 position:50% align:center
- Mr. Shirakaba,

00:18:51.923 --> 00:18:54.676 position:50% align:center
some of our students created
a movement seeking

00:18:54.759 --> 00:18:56.386 position:50% align:center
to overturn
a government decision.

00:18:56.469 --> 00:18:58.138 position:50% align:center
Did you know anything
about this?

00:18:58.221 --> 00:18:59.973 position:50% align:center
- It's been reported
on network news,

00:19:00.056 --> 00:19:02.017 position:50% align:center
and we've been getting
heavy pressure from the PTA.

00:19:02.100 --> 00:19:03.977 position:50% align:center
- How'd this happen,
Mr. Shirakaba?

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:06.604 position:50% align:center
- Those are students
in your homeroom class, correct?

00:19:07.147 --> 00:19:08.314 position:50% align:center
- Two months back,

00:19:08.398 --> 00:19:10.400 position:50% align:center
I directly advised three
of those students

00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:12.235 position:50% align:center
to stay away from that school.

00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:15.321 position:50% align:center
But now I regret that
I told them to do this.

00:19:15.405 --> 00:19:18.491 position:50% align:center
They've shown that
the old school is important.

00:19:18.575 --> 00:19:20.410 position:50% align:center
It surpasses the conveniences
of adults.

00:19:20.493 --> 00:19:22.704 position:50% align:center
The place matters
to the 24th ward.

00:19:22.787 --> 00:19:24.706 position:50% align:center
- [chuckles]
- Chairman.

00:19:24.789 --> 00:19:25.915 position:50% align:center
Can you help?

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:27.334 position:50% align:center
Could you convince
the government

00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:29.794 position:50% align:center
to acknowledge that
the Takara Elementary School

00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:31.504 position:50% align:center
is culturally worth preserving?

00:19:31.588 --> 00:19:34.382 position:50% align:center
Well, Mr. Shirakaba,

00:19:34.466 --> 00:19:36.926 position:50% align:center
I must say I'm thankful
that you buy so much into

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:38.553 position:50% align:center
the success of both my children.

00:19:38.636 --> 00:19:40.138 position:50% align:center
However,
considering my position,

00:19:40.221 --> 00:19:42.098 position:50% align:center
I must present
several conditions.

00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:43.391 position:50% align:center
 [glass shattering]

00:19:43.475 --> 00:19:45.727 position:50% align:center
- Don't go!
Wait till the guys get here!

00:19:45.810 --> 00:19:47.187 position:50% align:center
I just got off
the phone with them!

00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:49.814 position:50% align:center
- But if I don't go in right now
we can't save everybody!

00:19:50.398 --> 00:19:52.859 position:50% align:center
- Well, then I'll go in.
- Mari, please!

00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.486 position:50% align:center
- [whimpers]
- [grunts]

00:19:54.569 --> 00:19:56.196 position:50% align:center
All right.
I'll wait.

00:19:56.905 --> 00:19:58.531 position:50% align:center
Let's get ready to guide
the fire truck.

00:19:58.615 --> 00:20:00.075 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- And get onlookers out

00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:01.993 position:50% align:center
of the way.
- Uh, right.

00:20:02.077 --> 00:20:04.204 position:50% align:center
- Mari, hurry up!
- Okay!

00:20:04.287 --> 00:20:08.458 position:50% align:center
[breathing heavily]

00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.460 position:50% align:center
Mm?
Uh, Asumi?

00:20:10.543 --> 00:20:12.295 position:50% align:center
Asumi!
- I'm sorry,

00:20:12.379 --> 00:20:13.630 position:50% align:center
but we won't be able
to save everybody

00:20:13.713 --> 00:20:15.048 position:50% align:center
if we wait for the firefighters!

00:20:15.131 --> 00:20:17.133 position:50% align:center
- Please, no!

00:20:18.218 --> 00:20:19.469 position:50% align:center
Don't do this!

00:20:19.552 --> 00:20:21.346 position:50% align:center
You're not Shu, you know!

00:20:22.013 --> 00:20:23.640 position:50% align:center
You'll die.
[flames roaring]

00:20:27.852 --> 00:20:31.189 position:50% align:center
 I'm saving this footage onto
 my phone as a reminder.

00:20:31.272 --> 00:20:33.233 position:50% align:center
 I'll keep it
 for self admonishment.

00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:35.527 position:50% align:center
 So listen, future me.

00:20:35.610 --> 00:20:37.112 position:50% align:center
 Please don't forget.

00:20:37.195 --> 00:20:38.780 position:50% align:center
 Don't forget
 what happened today.

00:20:38.863 --> 00:20:40.323 position:50% align:center
[dog whining]

00:20:40.407 --> 00:20:43.118 position:50% align:center
You were always claiming it
was for everybody's sake.

00:20:43.201 --> 00:20:45.578 position:50% align:center
We kept saying it over and over

00:20:45.662 --> 00:20:47.956 position:50% align:center
and we kept acting
as if it were true.

00:20:48.039 --> 00:20:50.125 position:50% align:center
But why did you have
to die for it?

00:20:50.208 --> 00:20:52.335 position:50% align:center
[crying]

00:20:52.419 --> 00:20:55.338 position:50% align:center
[dog whining]

00:21:03.513 --> 00:21:04.556 position:50% align:center
[exhales sharply]

00:21:04.639 --> 00:21:06.599 position:50% align:center
So, already been a year?

00:21:07.434 --> 00:21:09.310 position:50% align:center
I can't do this.

00:21:09.394 --> 00:21:12.188 position:50% align:center
I can't keep striving
to match someone who's gone.

00:21:12.272 --> 00:21:13.982 position:50% align:center
Who do I think I am?

00:21:14.065 --> 00:21:16.276 position:50% align:center
I'm no better than Shu.

00:21:17.277 --> 00:21:20.947 position:50% align:center
Asumi, I can't look after RGB
without you.

00:21:21.031 --> 00:21:23.408 position:50% align:center
I can't deal with
the three of them by myself.

00:21:28.872 --> 00:21:30.040 position:50% align:center
Hey, Mom.
I'm home.

00:21:30.123 --> 00:21:31.082 position:50% align:center
- Welcome back, honey.

00:21:31.166 --> 00:21:32.083 position:50% align:center
You were out pretty late.

00:21:32.167 --> 00:21:33.376 position:50% align:center
- I was lost in thought
for a bit.

00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:34.711 position:50% align:center
- You kept us waiting, Mari.
- Huh?

00:21:34.794 --> 00:21:37.130 position:50% align:center
- We've started the tactical
meeting without you.

00:21:37.213 --> 00:21:38.506 position:50% align:center
- What's the deal?

00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:40.383 position:50% align:center
Why did you ask Ran
and Koki here, too?

00:21:40.467 --> 00:21:42.135 position:50% align:center
I alone should be plenty.

00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:43.636 position:50% align:center
- Are you insane?

00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:46.598 position:50% align:center
Mari is relying on my help.
You are just afterthoughts.

00:21:46.681 --> 00:21:48.433 position:50% align:center
- You think you can win against
little old me

00:21:48.516 --> 00:21:50.060 position:50% align:center
in coming up with ideas?

00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:51.895 position:50% align:center
- And good luck.
Go brainstorm.

00:21:51.978 --> 00:21:53.438 position:50% align:center
- [stammers]
Mm.

00:21:53.521 --> 00:21:55.190 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Mari, let's get started.
- Huh?

00:21:55.273 --> 00:21:57.067 position:50% align:center
- We've got to eat
something first, though.

00:21:57.150 --> 00:21:58.943 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:02.113 position:50% align:center
This is exactly what I mean
when I say RGB are so--

00:22:02.197 --> 00:22:05.116 position:50% align:center
okay, let's begin the Mari
special development meeting

00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:06.951 position:50% align:center
for the Gourmet Festival!

00:22:07.035 --> 00:22:09.579 position:50% align:center
- Man, I'm so full now.

00:22:09.662 --> 00:22:11.706 position:50% align:center
- All the blood's going
from my head to my stomach.

00:22:11.790 --> 00:22:14.167 position:50% align:center
- That was some taste test.
We overate.

00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:15.502 position:50% align:center
- [giggles]

00:22:15.585 --> 00:22:16.795 position:50% align:center
[plate rattling]

00:22:16.878 --> 00:22:17.921 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:22:18.004 --> 00:22:19.547 position:50% align:center
What are you--Asumi.

00:22:19.631 --> 00:22:21.091 position:50% align:center
- It's because of you, Mari.

00:22:21.174 --> 00:22:22.717 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- Everyone can be

00:22:22.801 --> 00:22:25.095 position:50% align:center
so mischievous because Itadaki
is around.

00:22:25.178 --> 00:22:26.304 position:50% align:center
[grunts]
Even if they're at odds

00:22:26.388 --> 00:22:27.931 position:50% align:center
with each other.

00:22:28.014 --> 00:22:30.266 position:50% align:center
There's always a place
for the guys to come back to.

00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:32.185 position:50% align:center
- You think so?
Really?

00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:33.687 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.

00:22:33.770 --> 00:22:35.563 position:50% align:center
You're the reason they're all
so close, Mari.

00:22:37.774 --> 00:22:39.776 position:50% align:center
- Well, I hope so.
Thanks.

00:22:39.859 --> 00:22:41.611 position:50% align:center
[water running]

00:22:41.695 --> 00:22:42.570 position:50% align:center
[faucet turns off]

00:22:42.654 --> 00:22:43.780 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Mari!

00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:45.407 position:50% align:center
It'll be sunny for GourFes.

00:22:45.490 --> 00:22:47.242 position:50% align:center
- Nice!

00:22:47.325 --> 00:22:48.743 position:50% align:center
[humming]

00:22:48.827 --> 00:22:50.537 position:50% align:center
All right,
let's do it.

